<LP>
   ZURICH -- ABB Asea Brown Boveri AG, the Swedish-Swiss
heavy engineering group, said it signed a joint venture
agreement with the Hungarian turbine manufacturer Lang
Gyepgyar.
   ABB will own 75% of a new company, to be called ABB Lang,
while Lang Gyepgyar will own 25%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company, which will begin operations in October 1990
and employ about 650 persons, will manufacture small and
medium-sized turbines. ABB will contribute technology for
steam turbines, as well as assist in structuring the
management of the new company, ABB said.
